1. *Vlasti* su donijele odluku o zabrani okupljanja. (The authorities have made a decision to ban gatherings.)
2. Naša *vlast* je uvela nove mjere za borbu protiv pandemije. (Our government has implemented new measures to fight against the pandemic.)
3. Oni su bili na *vlasti* deset godina. (They were in power for ten years.)
4. Većina građana nema povjerenja u *vlast*. (The majority of citizens don't trust the authorities.)
5. Mnogi se pitaju ko će preuzeti *vlast* nakon izbora. (Many wonder who will take over power after the elections.)
6. On je postao *vlast* u svom malom kraljevstvu. (He became the ruler in his small kingdom.)
7. Demonstranti su se pobunili protiv *vlasti*. (Protesters revolted against the authorities.)
8. *Vlasti* su podigle optužnicu protiv osumnjičenog za korupciju. (The authorities have filed charges against a corruption suspect.)
9. Svi se nadaju da će nova *vlast* poboljšati stanje u zemlji. (Everyone hopes that the new government will improve the situation in the country.)
10. Moraš se držati propisa koje su propisale *vlasti*. (You must abide by the regulations set by the authorities.)